The paper discusses a new approach to neuroevolution, which is a subfield of machine learning focused on evolving neural networks. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for a more powerful solution representation and a scalable searching algorithm, which are common challenges in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper tests the proposed approach on image classification problems, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
